President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Richard Howorth has been nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority. Harry K. Thomas, Jr. has been nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Zimbabwe, Department of State. Victoria Wassmer has been nominated for Under Secretary, Department of Energy. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Sandra E. Black as Member of the Council of Economic Advisers, Raymond Cook as Chief Information Officer of the Intelligence Community, Brooke D. Anderson as Member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board, Robert L. Stein as Member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board, Barbara Rimer as Chairman of the President's Cancer Panel, and Owen Witte as Member of the President's Cancer Panel. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and their dedication to their roles.